This paper proposes a stereo vision-based approach for tracking the camera ego-motion and 3D semantic objects in dynamic autonomous driving scenarios. The paper focuses on computer vision and robotics, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV and cs.RO sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel dynamic object bundle adjustment approach, which involves optimization and machine learning techniques, indicating that it could also belong to the cs.LG and cs.AI sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses semantic inference methods, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.CL sub-category.
